  Notwithstanding the fact that each multiple is determined by many
variables, there is a single variable that dominates when it comes to
explaining each multiple (and it is not the same variable for every
multiple). This variable is called the companion variable and is key to
finding undervalued stocks. In Table 4.4, the companion variables and
mismatches are identified for six multiples.
